<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-26T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="476" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d476">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/2415: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-26T19:00:00-05:00">December 26, 1934—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>111. Rio Pact has passed Colombian House of Representatives. Most of the
                            Conservatives were absent during the voting. Some hope is felt that it
                            may pass the Senate by similar methods.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>